Rating: 1
This is not carnitas. Get a good Mexican cookbook, Epicurious! My own version: take a good piece of pork, cover it with chicken or beef broth, add chopped garlic, onion, pepper (hot or sweet, your choice), tomato, a half teaspoon of chili powder (for gringos who don't like it too hot) some oregano and cumin. Cook pork until tender. It's good right out of the pot or fried as is the usual method to crisp it. Serve in warm authentic corn tortilla with avocado slices or just in its native state.

